article.headline: E. Michigan 70, Ohio 61
article.story: YPSILANTI, Mich. -- Carlos Medlock was just a point shy of tying his career best as he scored 31 points to lead Eastern Michigan past Ohio 70-61 on Saturday. It was Medlock's best performance since scoring 32 points against Davenport in November. The Eagles (12-11, 4-6 Mid-American) shot 48 percent from the field and took a 36-28 rebounding advantage over the Bobcats (12-11, 3-6). Brandon Bowdry snagged his 12th double-double of the season, scoring 17 points and pulling down 15 rebounds for the Eagles. Justin Dobbins also helped out with 12 points and 10 rebounds. Armon Bassett led the Bobcats in scoring with 19 points while D.J. Cooper added 15 points and Reggie Kelly finished with 11 points and eight rebounds.
